# Fix-Commit-Verify Loop

When fixing production issues, loop until `verify:prod` passes:

1. Fix on the topic branch.
2. Commit + push; complete the full ship bar (`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc` steps 4–9).
3. After merge and deploy: `npm run verify:prod -- --scope=auto --depth=smoke`.
4. If exit non-zero: fix, redeploy, re-run. Repeat until exit 0.

Never ask the user to run reproduction steps — perform all verification autonomously.
Do not consider the task done until production verification exits 0 or the user explicitly waives it.
